<paragraph blockId="12.[145,761,1509,1899]" lastBlockId="12.[809,1426,197,526]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis box="[145,283,1510,1531]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Mandible with a broadly truncate preapical tooth (this study; Supporting Information, 
<figureCitation box="[145,252,1570,1592]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[146,226,938,960]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,197,896]" captionTargetId="figure-470@8.[145,1425,195,898]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. Most-parsimonious tree (part two) from the EW analysis showing character state changes. Black rectangles represent unique changes and white rectangles represent homoplastic ones. Character numbers are indicated above branches and the corresponding state changes below the branches. Asterisks indicate type species of the genus. The position of Colletes clypeonitens is doubtful (see text). The Colletinae shown are (from top to bottom) Hemicotelles ruizii, C. cyanescens, C. nigritulus and C. slevini." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. S6D</figureCitation>
) is sufficient to distinguish the females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[176,341,1601,1622]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[176,341,1601,1622]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from those of the other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1841" box="[145,268,1632,1654]" pageId="12" pageNumber="199" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Colletinae">Colletinae</taxonomicName>
, in which the preapical tooth is narrowly rounded (Supporting Information, 
<figureCitation box="[582,688,1662,1684]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[146,226,938,960]" captionTargetBox="[146,1422,197,896]" captionTargetId="figure-470@8.[145,1425,195,898]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. Most-parsimonious tree (part two) from the EW analysis showing character state changes. Black rectangles represent unique changes and white rectangles represent homoplastic ones. Character numbers are indicated above branches and the corresponding state changes below the branches. Asterisks indicate type species of the genus. The position of Colletes clypeonitens is doubtful (see text). The Colletinae shown are (from top to bottom) Hemicotelles ruizii, C. cyanescens, C. nigritulus and C. slevini." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. S6C</figureCitation>
). The males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[250,407,1693,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[250,407,1693,1714]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed through the combination of mandible with apical tooth only slightly longer than preapical one (this study; Supporting Information, Fig. S15B) and T6 marginal zone not covered with pale tomentum (this study) [mandible with apical tooth distinctly longer than preapical one (Supporting Information, Fig. S15A) in both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[670,761,1877,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,761,1877,1898]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[866,1024,197,218]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,1024,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and T6 marginal zone covered with tomentum in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[1048,1228,228,249]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1048,1228,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1256,1425,228,249]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Mourecotelles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1425,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Mourecotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further differentiated from both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1281,1372,258,279]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1372,258,279]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[809,958,289,310]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[809,958,289,310]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by metapostnotum without transverse carina in both sexes (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation author="Michener CD" box="[1240,1418,320,342]" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" pagination="22 - 703" refId="ref12360" refString="Michener CD. 1989. Classification of American Colletinae (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 53: 22 - 703." type="journal article" year="1989">Michener, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[809,896,350,372]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="4.[146,225,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-197@4.[305,1265,195,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 4. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A, B, Lateral view of male propodeum, Trichocolletes dowerinensis (A) and Colletes gilvus (B); C–E, posterior view of male metapostnotum, Xanthocotelles atacama (C), Hemicotelles magallanes (D) and C. atripes (E); F, ventral view of male S7 of Mourecotelles sp.1. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) [metapostnotum with a transverse carina (
<figureCitation box="[818,939,381,403]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="4.[146,225,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,195,1390]" captionTargetId="figure-197@4.[305,1265,195,1392]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 4. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A, B, Lateral view of male propodeum, Trichocolletes dowerinensis (A) and Colletes gilvus (B); C–E, posterior view of male metapostnotum, Xanthocotelles atacama (C), Hemicotelles magallanes (D) and C. atripes (E); F, ventral view of male S7 of Mourecotelles sp.1. Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 4D, E</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[990,1083,381,402]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[990,1083,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1977" box="[1146,1297,381,402]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hemicotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1297,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Hemicotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[809,982,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[809,982,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having dark-brown to black hind tibia and basitarsus in both sexes (modified from: 
<bibRefCitation author="Toro H &amp; Cabezas V" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" pagination="131 - 148" refId="ref13033" refString="Toro H, Cabezas V. 1978. Nuevos generos y especies de Colletini sudamericanos (Apoidea Colletidae). Segunda parte. Anales del Museo de Historia Natural de Valpariso 11: 131 - 148." type="journal article" year="1978">Toro &amp; Cabezas, 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1011,1123,473,495]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[162,241,1151,1173]" captionTargetBox="[168,1439,199,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-337@1.[163,1443,195,1112]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Lateral habitus of some Colletinae showing some of their diversity. A–P, females, Hemicotelles magallanes (A), H. ruizii (B), Mourecotelles mixtus (C), Mourecotelles sp.1 (D), Xanthocotelles atacama (E), X. fritzi (F), Colletes cyanescens (G), C. cyaniventris (H), C. fulvipes (I), C. halophilus (J), C. nigritulus (K), C. petropolitanus (L), C. rugicollis (M), C. slevini (N), C. solidaginis (O) and C. zuluensis (P). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 1C, D</figureCitation>
) [legs pale-yellow to darkorange (
<figureCitation box="[901,1011,504,526]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="1.[162,241,1151,1173]" captionTargetBox="[168,1439,199,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-337@1.[163,1443,195,1112]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figure 1. Lateral habitus of some Colletinae showing some of their diversity. A–P, females, Hemicotelles magallanes (A), H. ruizii (B), Mourecotelles mixtus (C), Mourecotelles sp.1 (D), Xanthocotelles atacama (E), X. fritzi (F), Colletes cyanescens (G), C. cyaniventris (H), C. fulvipes (I), C. halophilus (J), C. nigritulus (K), C. petropolitanus (L), C. rugicollis (M), C. slevini (N), C. solidaginis (O) and C. zuluensis (P). Scale bars = 1 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Fig. 1E, F</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Toro &amp; Cabezas" authorityYear="1978" box="[1056,1220,504,525]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Xanthocotelles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1220,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="211">Xanthocotelles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
